# Architecture

## Purpose

Enforce the layered architecture so database, auth, and AI providers remain swappable.

## When It Applies

Every feature, refactor, or new package. Always read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` and `docs/BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE.md` before backend work.

## Requirements

- Apps consume packages; packages never import from apps.
- Application → Service → Repository (interface) → Adapter → External SDK.
- No Supabase/Prisma/OpenAI SDK imports in `apps/` or `packages/core`.
- UI components live in `@repo/ui`, not duplicated in apps.
- Shared types in `@repo/types`; infrastructure in `@repo/core`.

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ Service uses repository interface
class UserService extends BaseService {
  constructor(logger: Logger, private repo: BaseRepository<User>) {
    super(logger);
  }
}

// ✅ API route uses response helpers
return Response.json(createSuccessResponse(data));
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Direct SDK in a service
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

// ❌ UI component duplicated in apps/web/components/ui/
// ❌ Business logic inside a React component
```
